%% Diagram: Inventory reservation lifecycle (single-flight Lua + outbox)
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant U as User (admitted)
    participant API as Checkout API
    participant R as Redis (Lua single-flight)
    participant Q as Order queue (idempotent)
    participant W as Order worker
    participant DB as PostgreSQL (orders)

    U->>API: POST /checkout/start (checkout_token)
    API->>R: EVAL reserve_inventory.lua (sku, qty, ttl)
    R-->>R: GET stock; if stock >= qty: DECRBY + HSET reservation
    R-->>API: ok = true, reservation_id, remaining
    API-->>U: 201 reserved_until = now + TTL

    U->>API: POST /orders (session_id, payment_method)
    API->>Q: enqueue order (MessageDeduplicationId = idempotency_key)
    API-->>U: 202 Accepted, order_id

    W->>Q: receive (visibility timeout)
    W->>DB: INSERT order (idempotency_key UNIQUE)
    W->>W: charge payment (Idempotency-Key)
    alt payment success
        W->>R: HDEL reservation (confirm)
        W->>DB: UPDATE status = confirmed
    else payment failure / TTL expired
        W->>R: INCRBY stock (release)
        W->>DB: UPDATE status = failed
    end

    Note over R: Idle reservations expire via TTL ->> auto release.
